                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14641070" author="mosermw" created="Fri, 24 Jul 2015 21:06:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;developer-guide.html also says about OnStopped annotation &quot;Methods with this annotation must take zero arguments&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14703750" author="joewitt" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2015 21:08:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i&apos;ll review the patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14704003" author="joewitt" created="Wed, 19 Aug 2015 23:56:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Clearly this is an easy one and its cool that it appears resolve and the docs are fixed.  But def feels like we should have a unit test to verify/exercise this.  Although does all clean/compile and contrib-check is good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14704024" author="markap14" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 00:09:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=joewitt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;joewitt&quot;&gt;joewitt&lt;/a&gt;: Good call, I&apos;ve attached a patch that adds unit tests to ensure that it is functioning as designed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;br/&gt;
-Mark&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14704035" author="markap14" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 00:15:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also of note, the TestStandardProcessorTestRunner class was marked with @Ignore because the unit tests were largely designed to ensure that people were not using deprecated annotations, and the community decided to put off the failing of unit tests for a bit until people had a chance to change over their annotations. I created a new ticket, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-874&quot; title=&quot;Mock Framework should fail unit tests that use deprecated annotations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;NIFI-874&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;NIFI-874&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, to address that and just moved the @Ignore to each of the tests that previously existed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14704036" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 00:16:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 4f921931599f29e1554ca44b106cccf45fc85e22 in nifi&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=markap14&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;markap14&quot;&gt;markap14&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=nifi.git;h=4f92193&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=nifi.git;h=4f92193&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-787&quot; title=&quot;Mock framework should include ProcessContext to invocations of OnStopped for Processors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;NIFI-787&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;NIFI-787&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Ensure that Mock Framework passes a ProcessContext to methods using the @OnStopped annotation (if the method takes a ProcessContext object as an argument); updated developer guide to reflect that the object is allowed as an argument&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Signed-off-by: joewitt &amp;lt;joewitt@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14704038" author="joewitt" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 00:16:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Understood.  All good now.  I went ahead and pushed it myself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14704915" author="markap14" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 13:45:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Excellent, thanks for knocking that out, Joe!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
